title: Scrapbook (France), 1920s
inscribed: Some loose J. Claude Freres & Co. pages. Some fabrics identified as to type and structure with French labels.
description: Scrapbook, probably assembled in New York, containing 739 examples of French textiles and ribbons. There are several Egyptian revival ribbons.

tombstone.epitaph: Scrapbook (France), 1920s; silk; Closed book: 31 x 25.5 x 5.5 cm (12 3/16 x 10 1/16 x 2 3/16 in. ); 1967-54-4
